@startuml
title MAC Spoofing - Conceptual Flow

actor Attacker
participant "Attacker Device" as AD
participant "Switch / Local Network" as LAN
participant "Victim Device" as Victim
participant "Network Service" as Service

Victim ->> LAN: Communicate using legitimate MAC address
Attacker ->> AD: Change MAC address to victim's MAC
AD ->> LAN: Send frames using spoofed MAC address
LAN ->> Service: Forward traffic believing it is from victim device

note over AD
Attacker impersonates another
device at the data-link layer
inside the local network
end note

note over LAN
If the network relies on MAC identity,
it may confuse the attacker
with the legitimate device
end note

@enduml